tweets.text: It was 15 years ago today that Hurricane Charley slammed into southwest Florida as a Category 4 hurricane. It was projected to make landfall in Tampa Bay but ended up shifting to the east and sparing the Bay Area. Here's a look back at the major storm: https://t.co/LTgQTzebAi

Hurricane-savvy Floridians, I need your help. If you had to offer ONE TIP to a Florida newcomer to be ready during hurricane season, what would that one tip be? 🌨️

Answers could appear in a future @TB_Times story. Reply, DM me, or email gcalise@tampabay.com. https://t.co/DVA1gwoY6T

Back home, we have paralyzed one of the major highways as protest. @ricardorossello, we see not asking you to resign. We're kicking you out.

"Hurricane María took so much from us, that it took away our fears."

#CombátetePalCarajo
#RickyRenuncia https://t.co/OiLpZUtts3
